    {
      "id": "032d77a9aabed8312281d0cbb20aac39de02754c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2016-04-17 10:59:03.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThe test being changed is expected to fail for writes above 16TB, so only for ldiskfs. This isn't a limit for ZFS and the test should not fail there. \n\nThat said, the test does need to be fixed. Firstly, it should check that the FSTYPE is ldiskfs instead of checking that it isn't zfs. Your removal of getstripe is the right goal, but it could be done differently - check index 0, then force the file to be on OST0, or similar. Alternately, create the file on any OST first, then move the check after the file was created.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
